audit.actions:
1. MODIFY /Users/alexzh/platform-manager/bootstrap/claude-config/settings.json Add to enabledPlugins: "typescript-lsp@claude-plugins-official": true, "rust-analyzer-lsp@claude-plugins-official": true, "gopls-lsp@claude-plugins-official": true, "github@claude-plugins-official": true, "commit-commands@anthropics-claude-code": true, "agent-sdk-dev@claude-plugins-official": true (keeps custom .lsp.json for Bash/TOML/YAML/Lua which have no official plugin)
2. CREATE /Users/alexzh/platform-manager/.claude/settings.json Add project-level extraKnownMarketplaces so repo-trust propagates marketplaces to all surfaces automatically: { "extraKnownMarketplaces": { "neon": { ... }, "netlify-context-and-tools": { ... } } }
3. CREATE /Users/alexzh/platform-manager/hooks/hooks.json Migrate the PostToolUse and relevant lifecycle hooks from bootstrap settings.json into the plugin so they travel with plugin installation: { "hooks": { "PostToolUse": [ { "matcher": "Edit|Write", "hooks": [...] } ] } }
4. CREATE /Users/alexzh/platform-manager/commands/ directory Convert CLAUDE.md slash-command stubs (/check-cli-docs, /sdk-scaffold, /skill-audit, /quick, etc.) into proper Markdown command files so they appear in `/` autocomplete and benefit from `$ARGUMENTS` substitution.
5. CREATE /Users/alexzh/platform-manager/.claude-plugin/marketplace.json Register the plugin in a local marketplace so surfaces can install via: /plugin marketplace add anthropics/platform-manager (or local path) /plugin install platform-manager@platform-manager
